My team updated to the newest version of PathPlannerLib yesterday and since then we have been getting this error:

3:36:13.547 PM
at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.AutoBuilder.buildAuto(AutoBuilder.java:757) at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.AutoBuilder.getAutoCommandFromJson(AutoBuilder.java:773) at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.CommandUtil.commandFromJson(CommandUtil.java:46) at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.CommandUtil.sequentialGroupFromData(CommandUtil.java:81) ERROR 1 The startCompetition() method (or methods called by it) should have handled the exception above. edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:386) at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.CommandUtil.commandFromJson(CommandUtil.java:44) at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.CommandUtil.pathCommandFromData(CommandUtil.java:72) Warning 1 The robot program quit unexpectedly. This is usually due to a code error.
The above stacktrace can help determine where the error occurred.
See Reading Stacktraces — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation for more information. edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:379) at com.pathplanner.lib.path.PathPlannerPath.fromChoreoTrajectory(PathPlannerPath.java:402) Error at com.pathplanner.lib.path.PathPlannerPath.fromChoreoTrajectory(PathPlannerPath.java:402): Unhandled exception: java.lang.RuntimeException: java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke “org.json.simple.JSONArray.iterator()” because the return value of “org.json.simple.JSONObject.get(Object)” is null ERROR 1 Unhandled exception: java.lang.RuntimeException: java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke “org.json.simple.JSONArray.iterator()” because the return value of “org.json.simple.JSONObject.get(Object)” is null com.pathplanner.lib.path.PathPlannerPath.fromChoreoTrajectory(PathPlannerPath.java:402)

I have tried using an older version of PPLib as well as deleting all choreo related files entirely and it still has this error. The code builds fine but the robot starts bootlooping with this error.

tia
